<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,507,351,377]" box="[151,507,351,377]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,507,351,377]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="(Takakuwa, 1940)" baseAuthorityName="Takakuwa" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[151,507,351,377]" class="Chilopoda" family="Mecistocephalidae" genus="Arrup" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,507,351,377]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Arrup doii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Takakuwa, Y." box="[292,499,351,377]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refId="ref55954" refString="Takakuwa, Y. (1940) Fauna Nipponica 9 (8, 1). Geophilomorpha. Sanseido, Tokyo, 156 pp." type="book" year="1940">Takakuwa, 1940</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,426,812]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
This species was described from ‘Keizyo’ [= 
<collectingRegion box="[678,750,426,452]" country="South Korea" name="Seoul" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Seoul</collectingRegion>
], 
<collectingCountry box="[769,843,426,452]" name="South Korea" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Korea</collectingCountry>
, and then recorded from Honshu by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chamberlin, R. V. &amp; Wang, Y. M." pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="177 - 186" refId="ref53044" refString="Chamberlin, R. V. &amp; Wang, Y. M. (1952) Some records and descriptions of chilopods from Japan and other oriental areas. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 65, 177 - 186." type="journal article" year="1952">Chamberlin &amp; Wang (1952)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, K." box="[360,564,466,492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="187 - 190" refId="ref54889" refString="Shinohara, K. (1957) Taxonomical and morphological study on Myriapoda: I: Two new species of Chilopoda. Zoological Magazine, Tokyo, 66 (4), 187 - 190." type="journal article" year="1957">Shinohara (1957)</bibRefCitation>
and from 
<collectingCountry box="[686,772,466,492]" name="Taiwan" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, Y. M." box="[816,972,466,492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="195 - 199" refId="ref56749" refString="Wang, Y. M. (1959) Serica 1 j: On Chilopoda from Taiwan with a new lithobid. Quarterly Journal of the Taiwan Museum, 12, 195 - 199." type="journal article" year="1959">Wang (1959)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,426,812]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
The original description provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Takakuwa, Y." box="[637,842,506,532]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refId="ref55954" refString="Takakuwa, Y. (1940) Fauna Nipponica 9 (8, 1). Geophilomorpha. Sanseido, Tokyo, 156 pp." type="book" year="1940">Takakuwa (1940)</bibRefCitation>
is inadequate, as the diagnosis of this species was mainly based on the &quot;hairy&quot; surface of the mandibles. However, small scale­like or digitiform cuticular processes (similar to dense hair) on the ventral side of mandibles is a common feature among several mecistocephalids and is probably widely distributed in other centipedes. Presently, it is not possible to assess whether 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Takakuwa" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[252,329,666,691]" class="Chilopoda" family="Mecistocephalidae" genus="Arrup" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doii">
<emphasis box="[252,329,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. doii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is actually a distinct species, as no other clearly distinctive character emerges from the original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,426,812]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
In any case, records from 
<collectingCountry box="[513,579,746,772]" name="Japan" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[642,728,746,772]" name="Taiwan" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
are unwarranted, as they were based most probably on the presence of ‘hairy’ mandibles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
